```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant C as Client
  participant A as API A
  participant DB as Postgres
  participant N as NATS
  participant R as Redis
  participant B as API B

  C->>A: PUT /items/1 (new value)
  A->>DB: UPDATE items SET ...
  DB-->>A: OK
  A->>N: PUBLISH cache.invalidate {keys:[k1]}
  par Evict on A
    A->>A: Evict L1(k1)
    A->>R: DEL k1
  and Evict on B via event
    N-->>B: cache.invalidate {keys:[k1]}
    B->>B: Evict L1(k1)
    B->>R: DEL k1
  end
  A-->>C: 200 OK

  Note over C,B: Subsequent GETs on either instance miss cache and load fresh from DB.
```
